{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PDuTYL4kLPFpUvxkAAR7zn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Local lifecycle E2E test: create → join → resolve → claim.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Uses two isolated browser contexts (Player A and Player B) with\n     5→ * deterministic keypairs. The local validator has mock-VRF enabled,\n     6→ * and the randomness account is pre-loaded with fulfilled data\n     7→ * (byte[0] = 2 → HEADS → creator wins when they chose HEADS).\n     8→ *\n     9→ * Prerequisites (handled by localnet-bootstrap.sh):\n    10→ * - solana-test-validator running with coinflip + platform programs\n    11→ * - Orao mock accounts pre-loaded (network state, treasury, randomness)\n    12→ */\n    13→import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n    14→import * as po from \"./helpers/page-objects\";\n    15→import { fundTestWallets, PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\n    16→import { initializeLocalnet } from \"./helpers/localnet-setup\";\n    17→import {\n    18→  assertMatchCreated,\n    19→  assertMatchClosed,\n    20→  assertTreasuryFee,\n    21→  assertPlayerProfileDelta,\n    22→  snapshotBalance,\n    23→  snapshotPlayerProfile,\n    24→  getTreasuryAddress,\n    25→  calculateExpectedFee,\n    26→} from \"./helpers/on-chain\";\n    27→\n    28→// ── Suite setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    29→\n    30→test.beforeAll(async () => {\n    31→  // Fund test wallets and initialize program configs\n    32→  await fundTestWallets();\n    33→  await initializeLocalnet();\n    34→});\n    35→\n    36→// ── Full lifecycle test ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    37→\n    38→test(\"coinflip full lifecycle: create → join → resolve → claim\", async ({\n    39→  playerAPage,\n    40→  playerBPage,\n    41→  connection,\n    42→}) => {\n    43→  // On-chain constants for iron tier\n    44→  const TIER_IRON = 0;\n    45→  const SIDE_HEADS = 0;\n    46→  const ENTRY_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL in lamports\n    47→\n    48→  // Track console errors in both contexts\n    49→  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n    50→  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n    51→\n    52→  // 1. Player A navigates and creates a match (iron tier, heads)\n    53→  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n    54→  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n    55→\n    56→  // Player A should see the active match in \"waiting\" state\n    57→  await expect(\n    58→    playerAPage.locator(po.sel.activeMatchWaiting),\n    59→  ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n    60→\n    61→  // ── On-chain: verify match PDA after creation ──\n    62→  const { matchPda } = await assertMatchCreated(\n    63→    connection,\n    64→    PLAYER_A.publicKey,\n    65→    TIER_IRON,\n    66→    SIDE_HEADS,\n    67→  );\n    68→\n    69→  // 2. Player B navigates (after match is created) and sees it in the lobby\n    70→  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerBPage);\n    71→  await po.waitForLobbyMatch(playerBPage, 15_000);\n    72→\n    73→  // 3. Player B joins the match\n    74→  await po.joinMatch(playerBPage);\n    75→\n    76→  // ── On-chain: snapshot treasury + profiles before resolution/claim ──\n    77→  const treasury = await getTreasuryAddress(connection);\n    78→  const treasuryBefore = await snapshotBalance(connection, treasury);\n    79→  const profileABefore = await snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey);\n    80→  const profileBBefore = await snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey);\n    81→\n    82→  // 4. Both players wait for the result.\n    83→  //    VRF is pre-fulfilled (HEADS) → creator (Player A) wins.\n    84→  //    The frontend polls every 5s for VRF fulfillment, then shows\n    85→  //    a 3s flip animation before the \"complete\" phase.\n    86→  const [resultA, resultB] = await Promise.all([\n    87→    po.waitForResult(playerAPage, 30_000),\n    88→    po.waitForResult(playerBPage, 30_000),\n    89→  ]);\n    90→\n    91→  // 5. Verify results: Player A (creator, chose HEADS) should win\n    92→  expect(resultA).toBe(\"won\");\n    93→  expect(resultB).toBe(\"lost\");\n    94→\n    95→  // 6. Player A (winner) claims payout\n    96→  await po.claimOrSettle(playerAPage);\n    97→\n    98→  // Player A sees \"Back to Lobby\" after successful claim\n    99→  await expect(\n   100→    playerAPage.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" }),\n   101→  ).toBeVisible();\n   102→\n   103→  // ── On-chain: verify match PDA is closed after claim ──\n   104→  await assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda);\n   105→\n   106→  // ── On-chain: verify treasury received the 3% fee ──\n   107→  await assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, treasuryBefore, ENTRY_AMOUNT);\n   108→\n   109→  // ── On-chain: verify player profile updates ──\n   110→  const { payout } = calculateExpectedFee(ENTRY_AMOUNT);\n   111→\n   112→  // Player A (winner): +1 game, +1 win, wagered entry, won payout\n   113→  await assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, profileABefore, {\n   114→    totalGames: 1,\n   115→    wins: 1,\n   116→    totalWagered: ENTRY_AMOUNT,\n   117→    totalWon: payout,\n   118→  });\n   119→\n   120→  // Player B (loser): +1 game, +0 wins, wagered entry, won nothing\n   121→  await assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, profileBBefore, {\n   122→    totalGames: 1,\n   123→    wins: 0,\n   124→    totalWagered: ENTRY_AMOUNT,\n   125→    totalWon: 0,\n   126→  });\n   127→\n   128→  // 7. Player A returns to lobby\n   129→  await po.backToLobby(playerAPage);\n   130→\n   131→  // No unhandled console errors in either context\n   132→  consoleA.assertClean();\n   133→  consoleB.assertClean();\n   134→});\n   135→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"91ee5a7d-30c5-47c5-b622-e17ba25ea31a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HL2NbEg94bACcyWwZA7Nxi","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"4de5971a-85cb-491c-827f-f5935763a517"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HL2NbEg94bACcyWwZA7Nxi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Dual-browser-context fixture for devnet E2E tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Same isolated dual-player pattern as local fixtures, but connects\n     5→ * to the devnet RPC instead of a local validator. The RPC URL comes\n     6→ * from the validated devnet env config.\n     7→ *\n     8→ * Usage in tests:\n     9→ * ```ts\n    10→ * import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n    11→ *\n    12→ * test(\"devnet lifecycle\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => {\n    13→ *   // playerAPage and playerBPage target devnet via real RPC\n    14→ * });\n    15→ * ```\n    16→ */\n    17→import { test as base, type BrowserContext, type Page } from \"@playwright/test\";\n    18→import { Keypair, Connection } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    19→import { PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"../local/helpers/wallets\";\n    20→import { type DevnetConfig, validateDevnetEnv } from \"./helpers/env\";\n    21→\n    22→export interface DevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n    23→  /** Validated devnet configuration (RPC URL, program IDs). */\n    24→  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig;\n    25→  /** Isolated browser context for player A (keypair injected). */\n    26→  playerAContext: BrowserContext;\n    27→  /** Isolated browser context for player B (keypair injected). */\n    28→  playerBContext: BrowserContext;\n    29→  /** Page within player A's context. */\n    30→  playerAPage: Page;\n    31→  /** Page within player B's context. */\n    32→  playerBPage: Page;\n    33→  /** Player A's deterministic keypair. */\n    34→  playerAKeypair: Keypair;\n    35→  /** Player B's deterministic keypair. */\n    36→  playerBKeypair: Keypair;\n    37→  /** Shared RPC connection to the devnet cluster. */\n    38→  connection: Connection;\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→/**\n    42→ * Inject a 32-byte keypair seed into a new browser context via addInitScript.\n    43→ */\n    44→async function createPlayerContext(\n    45→  browser: BrowserContext[\"browser\"],\n    46→  keypair: Keypair,\n    47→): Promise<BrowserContext> {\n    48→  const context = await browser!.newContext();\n    49→  const seedArray = Array.from(keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 32));\n    50→  await context.addInitScript((seed: number[]) => {\n    51→    (window as unknown as Record<string, unknown>).__TEST_WALLET_SEED__ =\n    52→      new Uint8Array(seed);\n    53→  }, seedArray);\n    54→  return context;\n    55→}\n    56→\n    57→export const test = base.extend<DevnetDualPlayerFixtures>({\n    58→  // Validate devnet env once per test (sync, cached by Playwright)\n    59→  // eslint-disable-next-line no-empty-pattern\n    60→  devnetConfig: async ({}, use) => {\n    61→    const config = validateDevnetEnv();\n    62→    await use(config);\n    63→  },\n    64→\n    65→  // Expose keypairs as fixtures\n    66→  playerAKeypair: [PLAYER_A, { option: true }],\n    67→  playerBKeypair: [PLAYER_B, { option: true }],\n    68→\n    69→  // Shared connection to devnet\n    70→  connection: async ({ devnetConfig }, use) => {\n    71→    const conn = new Connection(devnetConfig.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n    72→    await use(conn);\n    73→  },\n    74→\n    75→  // --- Player A context + page ---\n    76→  playerAContext: async ({ browser, playerAKeypair }, use) => {\n    77→    const context = await createPlayerContext(browser, playerAKeypair);\n    78→    await use(context);\n    79→    await context.close();\n    80→  },\n    81→\n    82→  playerAPage: async ({ playerAContext }, use) => {\n    83→    const page = await playerAContext.newPage();\n    84→    await use(page);\n    85→  },\n    86→\n    87→  // --- Player B context + page ---\n    88→  playerBContext: async ({ browser, playerBKeypair }, use) => {\n    89→    const context = await createPlayerContext(browser, playerBKeypair);\n    90→    await use(context);\n    91→    await context.close();\n    92→  },\n    93→\n    94→  playerBPage: async ({ playerBContext }, use) => {\n    95→    const page = await playerBContext.newPage();\n    96→    await use(page);\n    97→  },\n    98→});\n    99→\n   100→export { expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\n   101→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"c065f117-9bdb-4a58-a274-7917238f5463"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XdqxtoMxD3AoiBgALh5YbU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"9062d3c1-92d1-4251-b31d-435b50721adc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XdqxtoMxD3AoiBgALh5YbU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Devnet E2E smoke test.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Validates the devnet environment contract (env vars + deployed programs)\n     5→ * and verifies the app loads against the devnet RPC.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n     8→import { verifyDevnetDeployments } from \"./helpers/env\";\n     9→\n    10→test.describe(\"devnet smoke\", () => {\n    11→  test(\"devnet deployments are reachable and valid\", async ({\n    12→    devnetConfig,\n    13→  }) => {\n    14→    // Verifies: RPC health, coinflip/platform/orao programs deployed, VRF initialized\n    15→    await verifyDevnetDeployments(devnetConfig);\n    16→  });\n    17→\n    18→  test(\"app loads against devnet\", async ({ playerAPage }) => {\n    19→    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    20→    // App should render the main layout (not a blank screen or error page)\n    21→    await expect(playerAPage.locator(\"body\")).not.toBeEmpty();\n    22→    // Navigation should be present (proves React rendered)\n    23→    await expect(\n    24→      playerAPage.locator(\"nav, [class*='sidebar'], [class*='nav']\").first(),\n    25→    ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n    26→  });\n    27→\n    28→  test(\"wallet connects with test keypair on devnet\", async ({\n    29→    playerAPage,\n    30→    playerAKeypair,\n    31→  }) => {\n    32→    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    33→    // Wait for wallet to auto-connect via TestWalletProvider\n    34→    const pubkeyShort = playerAKeypair.publicKey.toBase58().slice(0, 4);\n    35→    // The wallet address (or a truncated version) should appear somewhere in the UI\n    36→    await expect(playerAPage.getByText(pubkeyShort).first()).toBeVisible({\n    37→      timeout: 15_000,\n    38→    });\n    39→  });\n    40→});\n    41→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"2202bd32-4b81-4024-9ee0-a1a3d300c8bb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XY8AyPdguR3tGkWzc2R3g6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"142cf99f-767b-4522-99d4-09a06b9f77fb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XY8AyPdguR3tGkWzc2R3g6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Devnet E2E environment contract.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Validates that all required environment variables are present and well-formed\n     5→ * before any devnet test runs. Fails fast with clear error messages so CI\n     6→ * doesn't waste time on doomed runs.\n     7→ *\n     8→ * Required env vars:\n     9→ *   VITE_RPC_URL             — Devnet RPC endpoint (https URL)\n    10→ *   VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID — Deployed coinflip program address (base58)\n    11→ *   VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID — Deployed platform program address (base58)\n    12→ *\n    13→ * Optional (with defaults):\n    14→ *   VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK      — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\n    15→ */\n    16→\n    17→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    18→\n    19→// Orao VRF program ID (hardcoded — same address on all clusters)\n    20→const ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n    21→  \"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\",\n    22→);\n    23→\n    24→/** Validated devnet configuration. */\n    25→export interface DevnetConfig {\n    26→  rpcUrl: string;\n    27→  network: string;\n    28→  coinflipProgramId: PublicKey;\n    29→  platformProgramId: PublicKey;\n    30→  oraoVrfProgramId: PublicKey;\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→/** Validate a base58 public key string. Throws if invalid. */\n    34→function parsePublicKey(value: string, label: string): PublicKey {\n    35→  try {\n    36→    return new PublicKey(value);\n    37→  } catch {\n    38→    throw new Error(\n    39→      `${label} is not a valid Solana address (base58): \"${value}\"`,\n    40→    );\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n    44→/** Validate a URL string. Throws if malformed. */\n    45→function parseUrl(value: string, label: string): string {\n    46→  try {\n    47→    const url = new URL(value);\n    48→    if (![\"http:\", \"https:\"].includes(url.protocol)) {\n    49→      throw new Error(\"not http(s)\");\n    50→    }\n    51→    return value;\n    52→  } catch {\n    53→    throw new Error(\n    54→      `${label} is not a valid HTTP(S) URL: \"${value}\"`,\n    55→    );\n    56→  }\n    57→}\n    58→\n    59→/**\n    60→ * Read and validate all required devnet env vars.\n    61→ * Throws with a consolidated error listing every missing/invalid variable.\n    62→ */\n    63→export function validateDevnetEnv(): DevnetConfig {\n    64→  const errors: string[] = [];\n    65→\n    66→  // --- Required ---\n    67→  const rpcUrl = process.env.VITE_RPC_URL;\n    68→  if (!rpcUrl) {\n    69→    errors.push(\"VITE_RPC_URL is required (devnet RPC endpoint)\");\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  const coinflipId = process.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID;\n    73→  if (!coinflipId) {\n    74→    errors.push(\n    75→      \"VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID is required (deployed coinflip program address)\",\n    76→    );\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  const platformId = process.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID;\n    80→  if (!platformId) {\n    81→    errors.push(\n    82→      \"VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID is required (deployed platform program address)\",\n    83→    );\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  // Fail fast if any required var is missing\n    87→  if (errors.length > 0) {\n    88→    throw new Error(\n    89→      `Devnet E2E env validation failed:\\n  - ${errors.join(\"\\n  - \")}\\n\\n` +\n    90→        `Hint: copy .env.devnet to .env.local and update program IDs, ` +\n    91→        `or export the variables before running tests.`,\n    92→    );\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  // --- Format validation ---\n    96→  const validatedUrl = parseUrl(rpcUrl!, \"VITE_RPC_URL\");\n    97→  const coinflipProgramId = parsePublicKey(\n    98→    coinflipId!,\n    99→    \"VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\",\n   100→  );\n   101→  const platformProgramId = parsePublicKey(\n   102→    platformId!,\n   103→    \"VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\",\n   104→  );\n   105→\n   106→  // --- Optional with default ---\n   107→  const network = process.env.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK ?? \"devnet\";\n   108→\n   109→  return {\n   110→    rpcUrl: validatedUrl,\n   111→    network,\n   112→    coinflipProgramId,\n   113→    platformProgramId,\n   114→    oraoVrfProgramId: ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID,\n   115→  };\n   116→}\n   117→\n   118→/**\n   119→ * Verify that the devnet RPC is reachable and that required programs\n   120→ * are deployed. Call this once in globalSetup or the first test's beforeAll.\n   121→ */\n   122→export async function verifyDevnetDeployments(\n   123→  config: DevnetConfig,\n   124→): Promise<void> {\n   125→  const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n   126→\n   127→  // 1. RPC health check\n   128→  try {\n   129→    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n   130→  } catch (err) {\n   131→    throw new Error(\n   132→      `Cannot reach devnet RPC at ${config.rpcUrl}: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : err}`,\n   133→    );\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→  // 2. Coinflip program deployed\n   137→  const coinflipAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   138→    config.coinflipProgramId,\n   139→  );\n   140→  if (!coinflipAccount || !coinflipAccount.executable) {\n   141→    throw new Error(\n   142→      `Coinflip program not found or not executable at ${config.coinflipProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   143→    );\n   144→  }\n   145→\n   146→  // 3. Platform program deployed\n   147→  const platformAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   148→    config.platformProgramId,\n   149→  );\n   150→  if (!platformAccount || !platformAccount.executable) {\n   151→    throw new Error(\n   152→      `Platform program not found or not executable at ${config.platformProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   153→    );\n   154→  }\n   155→\n   156→  // 4. Orao VRF program deployed\n   157→  const oraoAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   158→    config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n   159→  );\n   160→  if (!oraoAccount || !oraoAccount.executable) {\n   161→    throw new Error(\n   162→      `Orao VRF program not found or not executable at ${config.oraoVrfProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   163→    );\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  // 5. Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF is initialized)\n   167→  const [oraoNetworkState] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n   168→    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n   169→    config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n   170→  );\n   171→  const networkState = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\n   172→  if (!networkState) {\n   173→    throw new Error(\n   174→      `Orao VRF network state PDA not found at ${oraoNetworkState.toBase58()} — ` +\n   175→        `VRF provider may not be initialized on this cluster`,\n   176→    );\n   177→  }\n   178→}\n   179→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"b99d7550-d88f-403c-87ab-f5a218556178"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AtWzX6T79ppVLLykGWNe4g","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"772506a1-af2e-481b-9519-27de241b274b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AtWzX6T79ppVLLykGWNe4g","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Shared E2E page-object helpers for coinflip tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * CSS-class-based selectors matching the actual component markup.\n     5→ * Provides create, join, claim, cancel actions and reusable wait/assert primitives.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { type Page, type Locator, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     8→\n     9→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    10→// Selectors (CSS classes from CoinflipPage, ActiveMatchView, OpenMatchesList)\n    11→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    12→\n    13→export const sel = {\n    14→  // Page structure\n    15→  lobby: \".coinflip-lobby\",\n    16→  sidebar: \".coinflip-sidebar\",\n    17→  main: \".coinflip-main\",\n    18→\n    19→  // Sidebar — create flow\n    20→  sidebarTitle: \".coinflip-sidebar__title\",\n    21→  tierSelector: \".rng-tier-selector\",\n    22→  tierButton: (tier: string) => `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--${tier})`,\n    23→  tierButtonSelected: \".rng-tier-btn--selected\",\n    24→  sideSelector: \".coinflip-side-selector\",\n    25→  sideButtonHeads: \".coinflip-side-btn--heads\",\n    26→  sideButtonTails: \".coinflip-side-btn--tails\",\n    27→  sideButtonSelected: \".coinflip-side-btn--selected\",\n    28→  summary: \".coinflip-sidebar__summary\",\n    29→  actionButton: \".coinflip-action-btn\",\n    30→  actionButtonSecondary: \".coinflip-action-btn--secondary\",\n    31→\n    32→  // Lobby — open matches\n    33→  matchesList: \".coinflip-matches__list\",\n    34→  matchesCount: \".coinflip-matches__count\",\n    35→  matchCard: \".coinflip-match-card\",\n    36→  matchCardOwn: \".coinflip-match-card--own\",\n    37→  matchCardClaimable: \".coinflip-match-card--claimable\",\n    38→  matchCardJoinBtn: \".coinflip-match-card__join-btn\",\n    39→  matchCardAmount: \".coinflip-match-card__amount\",\n    40→  matchCardAddress: \".coinflip-match-card__address\",\n    41→\n    42→  // Active match view\n    43→  activeMatch: \".coinflip-active-match\",\n    44→  activeMatchTitle: \".coinflip-active-match__title\",\n    45→  activeMatchTitleWon: \".coinflip-active-match__title--won\",\n    46→  activeMatchTitleLost: \".coinflip-active-match__title--lost\",\n    47→  activeMatchWaiting: \".coinflip-active-match__waiting\",\n    48→  activeMatchPlaying: \".coinflip-active-match__playing\",\n    49→\n    50→  // Result\n    51→  resultOutcome: \".coinflip-result__outcome\",\n    52→  resultPayout: \".coinflip-result__payout\",\n    53→\n    54→  // Post-claim\n    55→  postClaim: \".coinflip-active-match__post-claim\",\n    56→\n    57→  // Error\n    58→  errorToast: \".coinflip-error-toast\",\n    59→  toastMessage: \".rng-toast__message\",\n    60→\n    61→  // Sidebar — active match info\n    62→  sidebarStatus: \".coinflip-sidebar__status\",\n    63→  sidebarPot: \".coinflip-sidebar__pot\",\n    64→} as const;\n    65→\n    66→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    67→// Types\n    68→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    69→\n    70→export type CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\";\n    71→export type Tier =\n    72→  | \"iron\"\n    73→  | \"bronze\"\n    74→  | \"silver\"\n    75→  | \"gold\"\n    76→  | \"platinum\"\n    77→  | \"diamond\";\n    78→\n    79→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    80→// Page-object actions\n    81→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    82→\n    83→/**\n    84→ * Navigate to the coinflip page and wait for the lobby to render.\n    85→ */\n    86→export async function navigateToCoinflip(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n    87→  await page.goto(\"/coinflip\", { waitUntil: \"networkidle\" });\n    88→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.main, { state: \"visible\", timeout: 10_000 });\n    89→}\n    90→\n    91→/**\n    92→ * Select a tier in the sidebar tier selector.\n    93→ */\n    94→export async function selectTier(page: Page, tier: Tier): Promise<void> {\n    95→  await page.click(sel.tierButton(tier));\n    96→  await expect(page.locator(sel.tierButton(tier))).toHaveClass(/rng-tier-btn--selected/);\n    97→}\n    98→\n    99→/**\n   100→ * Select a coin side (heads or tails) in the sidebar.\n   101→ */\n   102→export async function selectSide(page: Page, side: CoinSide): Promise<void> {\n   103→  const selector =\n   104→    side === \"heads\" ? sel.sideButtonHeads : sel.sideButtonTails;\n   105→  await page.click(selector);\n   106→  await expect(page.locator(selector)).toHaveClass(/coinflip-side-btn--selected/);\n   107→}\n   108→\n   109→/**\n   110→ * Create a match: select tier, select side, click \"Create Game\".\n   111→ * Returns when the active match view (waiting state) is visible.\n   112→ */\n   113→export async function createMatch(\n   114→  page: Page,\n   115→  tier: Tier,\n   116→  side: CoinSide,\n   117→): Promise<void> {\n   118→  await selectTier(page, tier);\n   119→  await selectSide(page, side);\n   120→\n   121→  // Click create — button text is \"Create Game\"\n   122→  const createBtn = page.locator(sel.actionButton, {\n   123→    hasText: \"Create Game\",\n   124→  });\n   125→  await expect(createBtn).toBeEnabled();\n   126→  await createBtn.click();\n   127→\n   128→  // Wait for transition to active match (waiting for opponent)\n   129→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.activeMatch, {\n   130→    state: \"visible\",\n   131→    timeout: 15_000,\n   132→  });\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→/**\n   136→ * Join a match visible in the lobby. If `matchIndex` is provided, join that\n   137→ * specific card (0-based). Otherwise joins the first joinable match.\n   138→ */\n   139→export async function joinMatch(\n   140→  page: Page,\n   141→  matchIndex = 0,\n   142→): Promise<void> {\n   143→  const cards = page.locator(\n   144→    `${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardOwn}):not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`,\n   145→  );\n   146→  const joinBtn = cards.nth(matchIndex).locator(sel.matchCardJoinBtn);\n   147→  await expect(joinBtn).toBeEnabled({ timeout: 10_000 });\n   148→  await joinBtn.click();\n   149→\n   150→  // Wait for active match view to appear\n   151→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.activeMatch, {\n   152→    state: \"visible\",\n   153→    timeout: 15_000,\n   154→  });\n   155→}\n   156→\n   157→/**\n   158→ * Cancel the currently active match (phase = \"created\", waiting for opponent).\n   159→ * Clicks \"Cancel Match\" button in the ActiveMatchView.\n   160→ */\n   161→export async function cancelMatch(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   162→  const cancelBtn = page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Cancel Match\" });\n   163→  await expect(cancelBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 5_000 });\n   164→  await cancelBtn.click();\n   165→\n   166→  // Wait for lobby to reappear\n   167→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   168→    state: \"visible\",\n   169→    timeout: 15_000,\n   170→  });\n   171→}\n   172→\n   173→/**\n   174→ * Claim payout for the winner, or settle for the loser.\n   175→ * Clicks the \"Claim Payout\" or \"Settle & Return\" button in the sidebar.\n   176→ */\n   177→export async function claimOrSettle(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   178→  // The claim/settle button is in the sidebar (CoinflipPage renders it there)\n   179→  const claimBtn = page.locator(sel.sidebar).locator(sel.actionButton).first();\n   180→  await expect(claimBtn).toBeEnabled({ timeout: 15_000 });\n   181→  await claimBtn.click();\n   182→\n   183→  // Wait for \"Back to Lobby\" button to confirm claim completed\n   184→  await expect(\n   185→    page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" }),\n   186→  ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n   187→}\n   188→\n   189→/**\n   190→ * Click \"Back to Lobby\" to return after claiming.\n   191→ */\n   192→export async function backToLobby(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   193→  const btn = page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" });\n   194→  await expect(btn).toBeVisible();\n   195→  await btn.click();\n   196→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   197→    state: \"visible\",\n   198→    timeout: 10_000,\n   199→  });\n   200→}\n   201→\n   202→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   203→// Wait / assert primitives\n   204→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   205→\n   206→/**\n   207→ * Wait until the sidebar status text matches the expected phase label.\n   208→ * Phase labels: \"Waiting...\", \"Ready!\", \"Countdown...\", \"Flipping...\", \"Complete\"\n   209→ */\n   210→export async function waitForPhaseLabel(\n   211→  page: Page,\n   212→  label: string,\n   213→  timeout = 30_000,\n   214→): Promise<void> {\n   215→  await expect(page.locator(sel.sidebarStatus)).toHaveText(label, {\n   216→    timeout,\n   217→  });\n   218→}\n   219→\n   220→/**\n   221→ * Wait for the active match title to indicate a win or loss.\n   222→ */\n   223→export async function waitForResult(\n   224→  page: Page,\n   225→  timeout = 30_000,\n   226→): Promise<\"won\" | \"lost\"> {\n   227→  // Wait for either won or lost title class to appear\n   228→  const wonLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleWon);\n   229→  const lostLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleLost);\n   230→\n   231→  await expect(wonLocator.or(lostLocator)).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   232→\n   233→  if (await wonLocator.isVisible()) return \"won\";\n   234→  return \"lost\";\n   235→}\n   236→\n   237→/**\n   238→ * Wait for a match to appear in the lobby's open match list.\n   239→ */\n   240→export async function waitForLobbyMatch(\n   241→  page: Page,\n   242→  timeout = 15_000,\n   243→): Promise<Locator> {\n   244→  const card = page.locator(\n   245→    `${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`,\n   246→  ).first();\n   247→  await expect(card).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   248→  return card;\n   249→}\n   250→\n   251→/**\n   252→ * Assert the lobby is empty (no open matches).\n   253→ */\n   254→export async function assertLobbyEmpty(\n   255→  page: Page,\n   256→  timeout = 10_000,\n   257→): Promise<void> {\n   258→  // Either the empty state text or zero non-claimable match cards\n   259→  await expect(\n   260→    page.locator(`${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`),\n   261→  ).toHaveCount(0, { timeout });\n   262→}\n   263→\n   264→/**\n   265→ * Assert that an error toast is visible with the given message substring.\n   266→ */\n   267→export async function assertErrorToast(\n   268→  page: Page,\n   269→  messageSubstring: string,\n   270→  timeout = 5_000,\n   271→): Promise<void> {\n   272→  const toast = page.locator(sel.errorToast);\n   273→  await expect(toast).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   274→  await expect(toast).toContainText(messageSubstring);\n   275→}\n   276→\n   277→/**\n   278→ * Assert that no error toasts are visible.\n   279→ */\n   280→export async function assertNoErrorToast(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   281→  await expect(page.locator(sel.errorToast)).toHaveCount(0);\n   282→}\n   283→\n   284→/**\n   285→ * Get the current balance displayed or fetched from connection for a wallet.\n   286→ * This is a convenience wrapper for reading SOL balance via RPC, not UI-based.\n   287→ */\n   288→export async function getSolBalance(\n   289→  page: Page,\n   290→  walletAddress: string,\n   291→  rpcUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n   292→): Promise<number> {\n   293→  return page.evaluate(\n   294→    async ({ address, rpc }) => {\n   295→      const res = await fetch(rpc, {\n   296→        method: \"POST\",\n   297→        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n   298→        body: JSON.stringify({\n   299→          jsonrpc: \"2.0\",\n   300→          id: 1,\n   301→          method: \"getBalance\",\n   302→          params: [address, { commitment: \"confirmed\" }],\n   303→        }),\n   304→      });\n   305→      const json = await res.json();\n   306→      return (json.result?.value ?? 0) / 1_000_000_000;\n   307→    },\n   308→    { address: walletAddress, rpc: rpcUrl },\n   309→  );\n   310→}\n   311→\n   312→/**\n   313→ * Collect console errors from a page. Returns a cleanup function\n   314→ * and an array that accumulates errors.\n   315→ */\n   316→export function trackConsoleErrors(page: Page): {\n   317→  errors: string[];\n   318→  assertClean: () => void;\n   319→} {\n   320→  const errors: string[] = [];\n   321→  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n   322→    if (msg.type() === \"error\") errors.push(msg.text());\n   323→  });\n   324→  return {\n   325→    errors,\n   326→    assertClean: () => {\n   327→      // Filter out known non-critical browser noise\n   328→      const real = errors.filter(\n   329→        (e) =>\n   330→          !e.includes(\"favicon.ico\") &&\n   331→          !e.includes(\"downloadable font\") &&\n   332→          !e.includes(\"third-party cookie\"),\n   333→      );\n   334→      expect(real).toEqual([]);\n   335→    },\n   336→  };\n   337→}\n   338→\n   339→/**\n   340→ * Wait for a specific text to appear anywhere on the page.\n   341→ */\n   342→export async function waitForText(\n   343→  page: Page,\n   344→  text: string,\n   345→  timeout = 10_000,\n   346→): Promise<void> {\n   347→  await expect(page.getByText(text).first()).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   348→}\n   349→\n   350→/**\n   351→ * Wait for the lobby to be visible (no active match).\n   352→ */\n   353→export async function waitForLobby(\n   354→  page: Page,\n   355→  timeout = 15_000,\n   356→): Promise<void> {\n   357→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   358→    state: \"visible\",\n   359→    timeout,\n   360→  });\n   361→}\n   362→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"d1535def-bdc9-4609-90d2-73588e287267"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01N35wvGgVaRWQzyQhYaQFGu","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"04ab555e-4d03-4dca-ad4d-4584680883b4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N35wvGgVaRWQzyQhYaQFGu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * On-chain assertion helpers for local E2E tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Provides RPC-based helpers to query and assert match PDA state,\n     5→ * treasury fee deltas, and player profile stat updates.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     8→import { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n     9→import {\n    10→  CoinflipIDL,\n    11→  PlatformIDL,\n    12→  type Coinflip,\n    13→  type Platform,\n    14→} from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n    15→\n    16→// ============ Program IDs ============\n    17→\n    18→/** Coinflip program address (from IDL). */\n    19→export const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\n    20→\n    21→/** Platform program address (from IDL). */\n    22→export const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n    23→\n    24→/** Platform fee: 300 basis points = 3%. */\n    25→export const FEE_BPS = 300;\n    26→\n    27→// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n    28→\n    29→/** Derive the match PDA for a creator. Seeds: [\"match\", creator]. */\n    30→export function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n    31→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    32→    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    33→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n    34→  );\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→/** Derive the coinflip config PDA. Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]. */\n    38→export function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n    39→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    40→    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    41→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n    42→  );\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→/** Derive a player profile PDA. Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]. */\n    46→export function getPlayerProfilePda(wallet: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n    47→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    48→    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), wallet.toBuffer()],\n    49→    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n    50→  );\n    51→}\n    52→\n    53→// ============ Program Instances ============\n    54→\n    55→/**\n    56→ * Create a read-only Coinflip program instance.\n    57→ *\n    58→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    59→ */\n    60→export function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n    61→  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    62→    connection,\n    63→    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    64→    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n    65→  );\n    66→  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→/**\n    70→ * Create a read-only Platform program instance.\n    71→ *\n    72→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    73→ */\n    74→export function getPlatformProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Platform> {\n    75→  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    76→    connection,\n    77→    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    78→    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n    79→  );\n    80→  return new Program(PlatformIDL as Idl as Platform, provider);\n    81→}\n    82→\n    83→// ============ Account Types ============\n    84→\n    85→/** Deserialized match account shape. */\n    86→export interface MatchAccount {\n    87→  creator: PublicKey;\n    88→  opponent: PublicKey;\n    89→  tier: number;\n    90→  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n    91→  creatorSide: number;\n    92→  phase: Record<string, object>;\n    93→  result: number;\n    94→  winner: PublicKey;\n    95→  claimed: boolean;\n    96→  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    97→  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    98→  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n    99→  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n   100→  bump: number;\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→/** Deserialized player profile account shape. */\n   104→export interface PlayerProfileAccount {\n   105→  authority: PublicKey;\n   106→  totalGames: { toNumber(): number };\n   107→  wins: { toNumber(): number };\n   108→  totalWagered: { toNumber(): number };\n   109→  totalWon: { toNumber(): number };\n   110→  bump: number;\n   111→}\n   112→\n   113→// ============ Fetch Helpers ============\n   114→\n   115→/**\n   116→ * Fetch a match PDA account. Returns null if the account is closed.\n   117→ *\n   118→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   119→ * @param matchPda - The match PDA address\n   120→ */\n   121→export async function fetchMatch(\n   122→  connection: Connection,\n   123→  matchPda: PublicKey,\n   124→): Promise<MatchAccount | null> {\n   125→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   126→  try {\n   127→    return (await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(\n   128→      matchPda,\n   129→    )) as unknown as MatchAccount;\n   130→  } catch {\n   131→    // Account not found (closed or never created)\n   132→    return null;\n   133→  }\n   134→}\n   135→\n   136→/**\n   137→ * Fetch a player profile PDA account. Returns null if it doesn't exist.\n   138→ *\n   139→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   140→ * @param profilePda - The player profile PDA address\n   141→ */\n   142→export async function fetchPlayerProfile(\n   143→  connection: Connection,\n   144→  profilePda: PublicKey,\n   145→): Promise<PlayerProfileAccount | null> {\n   146→  const program = getPlatformProgram(connection);\n   147→  try {\n   148→    return (await program.account.playerProfile.fetch(\n   149→      profilePda,\n   150→    )) as unknown as PlayerProfileAccount;\n   151→  } catch {\n   152→    return null;\n   153→  }\n   154→}\n   155→\n   156→/**\n   157→ * Get the treasury wallet address from the coinflip config PDA.\n   158→ *\n   159→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   160→ */\n   161→export async function getTreasuryAddress(\n   162→  connection: Connection,\n   163→): Promise<PublicKey> {\n   164→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   165→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   166→  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n   167→  return (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n   168→}\n   169→\n   170→// ============ Balance Helpers ============\n   171→\n   172→/**\n   173→ * Get the SOL balance of an address in lamports.\n   174→ *\n   175→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   176→ * @param address - Public key to check\n   177→ */\n   178→export async function getBalanceLamports(\n   179→  connection: Connection,\n   180→  address: PublicKey,\n   181→): Promise<number> {\n   182→  return connection.getBalance(address);\n   183→}\n   184→\n   185→/**\n   186→ * Capture a balance snapshot for later delta comparison.\n   187→ *\n   188→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   189→ * @param address - Public key to snapshot\n   190→ */\n   191→export async function snapshotBalance(\n   192→  connection: Connection,\n   193→  address: PublicKey,\n   194→): Promise<number> {\n   195→  return connection.getBalance(address);\n   196→}\n   197→\n   198→// ============ Fee Calculation ============\n   199→\n   200→/**\n   201→ * Calculate the expected fee and net payout for a coinflip match.\n   202→ * Mirrors on-chain logic: fee = floor(pool * FEE_BPS / 10_000).\n   203→ *\n   204→ * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n   205→ * @returns Object with pool, fee, and payout amounts in lamports\n   206→ */\n   207→export function calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount: number): {\n   208→  pool: number;\n   209→  fee: number;\n   210→  payout: number;\n   211→} {\n   212→  const pool = entryAmount * 2;\n   213→  const fee = Math.floor((pool * FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   214→  const payout = pool - fee;\n   215→  return { pool, fee, payout };\n   216→}\n   217→\n   218→// ============ Assertion Helpers ============\n   219→\n   220→/**\n   221→ * Assert match PDA state after creation (Waiting phase).\n   222→ *\n   223→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   224→ * @param creator - Creator's public key\n   225→ * @param expectedTier - Expected tier index\n   226→ * @param expectedSide - Expected creator side (0 = heads, 1 = tails)\n   227→ */\n   228→export async function assertMatchCreated(\n   229→  connection: Connection,\n   230→  creator: PublicKey,\n   231→  expectedTier: number,\n   232→  expectedSide: number,\n   233→): Promise<{ matchPda: PublicKey; match: MatchAccount }> {\n   234→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   235→  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   236→  if (!match) throw new Error(`Match PDA not found for creator ${creator}`);\n   237→\n   238→  const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n   239→  if (phase !== \"waiting\") {\n   240→    throw new Error(`Expected phase 'waiting', got '${phase}'`);\n   241→  }\n   242→  if (match.creator.toBase58() !== creator.toBase58()) {\n   243→    throw new Error(\"Match creator does not match expected creator\");\n   244→  }\n   245→  if (match.tier !== expectedTier) {\n   246→    throw new Error(`Expected tier ${expectedTier}, got ${match.tier}`);\n   247→  }\n   248→  if (match.creatorSide !== expectedSide) {\n   249→    throw new Error(`Expected side ${expectedSide}, got ${match.creatorSide}`);\n   250→  }\n   251→  if (match.opponent.toBase58() !== PublicKey.default.toBase58()) {\n   252→    throw new Error(\"Expected no opponent in waiting phase\");\n   253→  }\n   254→  if (match.claimed) {\n   255→    throw new Error(\"Expected claimed=false after creation\");\n   256→  }\n   257→\n   258→  return { matchPda, match };\n   259→}\n   260→\n   261→/**\n   262→ * Assert match PDA is closed (account no longer exists).\n   263→ *\n   264→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   265→ * @param matchPda - The match PDA address to check\n   266→ */\n   267→export async function assertMatchClosed(\n   268→  connection: Connection,\n   269→  matchPda: PublicKey,\n   270→): Promise<void> {\n   271→  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   272→  if (match !== null) {\n   273→    const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n   274→    throw new Error(\n   275→      `Expected match PDA to be closed, but it still exists (phase: ${phase})`,\n   276→    );\n   277→  }\n   278→}\n   279→\n   280→/**\n   281→ * Assert that the treasury received the expected fee.\n   282→ * Call snapshotBalance before the payout, then call this after.\n   283→ *\n   284→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   285→ * @param treasury - Treasury public key\n   286→ * @param balanceBefore - Treasury balance in lamports before claim\n   287→ * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n   288→ */\n   289→export async function assertTreasuryFee(\n   290→  connection: Connection,\n   291→  treasury: PublicKey,\n   292→  balanceBefore: number,\n   293→  entryAmount: number,\n   294→): Promise<void> {\n   295→  const balanceAfter = await getBalanceLamports(connection, treasury);\n   296→  const { fee } = calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount);\n   297→  const actualDelta = balanceAfter - balanceBefore;\n   298→\n   299→  if (actualDelta !== fee) {\n   300→    throw new Error(\n   301→      `Treasury fee mismatch: expected ${fee} lamports, got delta ${actualDelta}`,\n   302→    );\n   303→  }\n   304→}\n   305→\n   306→/**\n   307→ * Assert player profile stats after a game.\n   308→ *\n   309→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   310→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   311→ * @param expected - Expected stat values\n   312→ */\n   313→export async function assertPlayerProfile(\n   314→  connection: Connection,\n   315→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   316→  expected: {\n   317→    totalGames: number;\n   318→    wins: number;\n   319→    totalWagered: number;\n   320→    totalWon: number;\n   321→  },\n   322→): Promise<void> {\n   323→  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n   324→  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n   325→  if (!profile) {\n   326→    throw new Error(`Player profile not found for ${wallet}`);\n   327→  }\n   328→\n   329→  const actual = {\n   330→    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n   331→    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n   332→    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n   333→    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n   334→  };\n   335→\n   336→  for (const key of Object.keys(expected) as (keyof typeof expected)[]) {\n   337→    if (actual[key] !== expected[key]) {\n   338→      throw new Error(\n   339→        `Profile ${key} mismatch for ${wallet}: expected ${expected[key]}, got ${actual[key]}`,\n   340→      );\n   341→    }\n   342→  }\n   343→}\n   344→\n   345→/**\n   346→ * Assert player profile stats changed by a specific delta since a snapshot.\n   347→ *\n   348→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   349→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   350→ * @param before - Profile stats snapshot before the action\n   351→ * @param delta - Expected stat deltas\n   352→ */\n   353→export async function assertPlayerProfileDelta(\n   354→  connection: Connection,\n   355→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   356→  before: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n   357→  delta: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n   358→): Promise<void> {\n   359→  const expected = {\n   360→    totalGames: before.totalGames + delta.totalGames,\n   361→    wins: before.wins + delta.wins,\n   362→    totalWagered: before.totalWagered + delta.totalWagered,\n   363→    totalWon: before.totalWon + delta.totalWon,\n   364→  };\n   365→  await assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected);\n   366→}\n   367→\n   368→/**\n   369→ * Snapshot a player profile's current stats (for later delta comparison).\n   370→ * Returns zero-stats if the profile doesn't exist yet.\n   371→ *\n   372→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   373→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   374→ */\n   375→export async function snapshotPlayerProfile(\n   376→  connection: Connection,\n   377→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   378→): Promise<{ totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number }> {\n   379→  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n   380→  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n   381→  if (!profile) {\n   382→    return { totalGames: 0, wins: 0, totalWagered: 0, totalWon: 0 };\n   383→  }\n   384→  return {\n   385→    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n   386→    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n   387→    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n   388→    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n   389→  };\n   390→}\n   391→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"7b7f59fd-fbdc-4145-85a6-f1bc7c39c3d5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FPFnnzoKbRE5MsH8XpWqgW","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"d3813476-e8b8-4dda-92f5-741c31d050cf"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FPFnnzoKbRE5MsH8XpWqgW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Deterministic wallet-funding helper for local E2E tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Generates fixed keypairs from seed bytes so tests are reproducible,\n     5→ * then airdrops SOL and confirms before tests run.\n     6→ */\n     7→import {\n     8→  Connection,\n     9→  Keypair,\n    10→  LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    11→  PublicKey,\n    12→} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    13→\n    14→// --- Deterministic keypairs ---\n    15→// Fixed 32-byte seeds produce the same keypairs on every run.\n    16→const SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);\n    17→const SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);\n    18→\n    19→export const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\n    20→export const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n    21→\n    22→/** Default RPC URL for local test validator. */\n    23→export const LOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n    24→\n    25→/** Default airdrop amount per wallet (10 SOL). */\n    26→const DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL = 10;\n    27→\n    28→/**\n    29→ * Airdrop SOL to a single wallet and confirm the transaction.\n    30→ *\n    31→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    32→ * @param to - Public key to fund\n    33→ * @param solAmount - Amount in SOL (default: 10)\n    34→ */\n    35→export async function fundWallet(\n    36→  connection: Connection,\n    37→  to: PublicKey,\n    38→  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n    39→): Promise<void> {\n    40→  const lamports = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n    41→  const sig = await connection.requestAirdrop(to, lamports);\n    42→  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n    43→    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n    44→  await connection.confirmTransaction(\n    45→    { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n    46→    \"confirmed\",\n    47→  );\n    48→}\n    49→\n    50→/**\n    51→ * Fund both test players on the local validator.\n    52→ * Call this in a `beforeAll` or global setup before the E2E suite starts.\n    53→ *\n    54→ * @param rpcUrl - RPC endpoint (default: local validator)\n    55→ * @param solAmount - SOL to airdrop per player (default: 10)\n    56→ */\n    57→export async function fundTestWallets(\n    58→  rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL,\n    59→  solAmount = DEFAULT_AIRDROP_SOL,\n    60→): Promise<{ playerA: Keypair; playerB: Keypair; connection: Connection }> {\n    61→  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n    62→\n    63→  await Promise.all([\n    64→    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, solAmount),\n    65→    fundWallet(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, solAmount),\n    66→  ]);\n    67→\n    68→  // Sanity-check: verify balances are present\n    69→  const [balA, balB] = await Promise.all([\n    70→    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_A.publicKey),\n    71→    connection.getBalance(PLAYER_B.publicKey),\n    72→  ]);\n    73→\n    74→  const minExpected = solAmount * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n    75→  if (balA < minExpected) {\n    76→    throw new Error(\n    77→      `Player A funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balA}`,\n    78→    );\n    79→  }\n    80→  if (balB < minExpected) {\n    81→    throw new Error(\n    82→      `Player B funding failed: expected >= ${minExpected} lamports, got ${balB}`,\n    83→    );\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  return { playerA: PLAYER_A, playerB: PLAYER_B, connection };\n    87→}\n    88→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"d6bee635-3bec-4ba8-81d9-80b78ea34d34"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0167CBkzC6AJtLBc51VVaaeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UNaGrTGfbNaRqKP9K7yJFo","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4324,"cache_read_input_tokens":20451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4324},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"5ac0ec66-116f-498c-acdf-7f2f1b4d0a2f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UNaGrTGfbNaRqKP9K7yJFo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { defineConfig, devices } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Playwright config for devnet E2E integration tests.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * Runs against deployed devnet contracts with real VRF fulfillment.\n     7→ * Does NOT start a local validator or deploy programs — requires\n     8→ * pre-deployed contracts and env vars (see e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts).\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Required env vars (set before running, or in .env.devnet):\n    11→ *   VITE_RPC_URL                — Devnet RPC endpoint\n    12→ *   VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID   — Deployed coinflip program address\n    13→ *   VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID   — Deployed platform program address\n    14→ *\n    15→ * Optional:\n    16→ *   VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK        — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\n    17→ */\n    18→export default defineConfig({\n    19→  testDir: \"./e2e\",\n    20→  fullyParallel: false,\n    21→  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,\n    22→  retries: 0,\n    23→  workers: 1,\n    24→  reporter: \"list\",\n    25→  // Longer timeout: real VRF fulfillment can take 30–60+ seconds\n    26→  timeout: 120_000,\n    27→\n    28→  use: {\n    29→    baseURL: \"http://localhost:3003\",\n    30→    screenshot: \"off\",\n    31→    trace: \"retain-on-failure\",\n    32→    ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"],\n    33→    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },\n    34→  },\n    35→\n    36→  projects: [\n    37→    {\n    38→      name: \"devnet-e2e\",\n    39→      testMatch: \"devnet/**/*.spec.ts\",\n    40→      use: {\n    41→        ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"],\n    42→        viewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 },\n    43→      },\n    44→    },\n    45→  ],\n    46→\n    47→  webServer: {\n    48→    command: \"npx vite --port 3003\",\n    49→    url: \"http://localhost:3003\",\n    50→    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,\n    51→    timeout: 30_000,\n    52→    env: {\n    53→      VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",\n    54→      VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",\n    55→      // RPC URL and program IDs are inherited from the process environment.\n    56→      // They must be set before running this config (see env.ts validation).\n    57→      // VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK defaults to \"devnet\" in the app if not set.\n    58→    },\n    59→  },\n    60→});\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"07529129-3ac7-45bc-9a8b-826e993a2aea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBVqT4TVpTf6w84fcLdqcK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the files. Let me now provide you with a comprehensive summary of the E2E test patterns.\n\n---\n\n## E2E Test Patterns Summary\n\n### Overview\nThe codebase uses **Playwright** for E2E testing with two distinct modes:\n1. **Local**: Uses a local Solana validator with mock VRF\n2. **Devnet**: Connects to real devnet RPC with actual VRF fulfillment\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Local Lifecycle Test** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Full game flow validation (create → join → resolve → claim) with deterministic outcomes.\n\n**Architecture**:\n- **Two isolated browser contexts** (Player A and Player B) via Playwright fixtures\n- **Deterministic keypairs**: Fixed 32-byte seeds (0xaa, 0xbb) produce same keys every run\n- **Mock VRF**: Local validator has Orao mock enabled; randomness account is pre-loaded with `byte[0] = 2` (HEADS)\n- **Pre-setup**: `test.beforeAll()` funds both players via airdrop\n\n**Test Flow**:\n```\n1. Player A navigates to coinflip\n2. Player A creates match (iron tier, HEADS)\n3. On-chain: assertMatchCreated() → verify match PDA exists\n4. Player B navigates and sees match in lobby\n5. Player B joins\n6. On-chain: snapshot treasury + player profiles\n7. Both wait for result (VRF pre-fulfilled)\n8. Verify: A won (chose HEADS), B lost\n9. Player A claims payout\n10. On-chain: assertMatchClosed() + assertTreasuryFee() + assertPlayerProfileDelta()\n11. Player A returns to lobby\n```\n\n**Key Constants**:\n- `TIER_IRON = 0`\n- `SIDE_HEADS = 0`\n- `ENTRY_AMOUNT = 5_000_000` (0.005 SOL)\n- VRF polling: 5s intervals; 3s flip animation before \"complete\" phase\n\n**On-Chain Assertions**:\n- Match PDA state changes (phase, opponent, claimed flag)\n- Treasury receives 3% fee (300 bps)\n- Player profiles updated: `totalGames`, `wins`, `totalWagered`, `totalWon`\n\n---\n\n## 2. **Devnet Fixtures** (`fixtures.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Dual-player fixture for devnet E2E tests (mirrors local pattern).\n\n**Key Difference**: Connects to devnet RPC instead of local validator.\n\n**Fixture Providers**:\n```typescript\ninterface DevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig           // Validated RPC + program IDs\n  playerAContext: BrowserContext       // Isolated context A\n  playerBContext: BrowserContext       // Isolated context B\n  playerAPage: Page                    // Page within A's context\n  playerBPage: Page                    // Page within B's context\n  playerAKeypair: Keypair              // PLAYER_A (0xaa seed)\n  playerBKeypair: Keypair              // PLAYER_B (0xbb seed)\n  connection: Connection               // Shared devnet RPC connection\n}\n```\n\n**Keypair Injection**:\n```typescript\n// Inject 32-byte seed into browser context via addInitScript\nawait context.addInitScript((seed: number[]) => {\n  (window as unknown as Record<string, unknown>).__TEST_WALLET_SEED__ =\n    new Uint8Array(seed);\n}, seedArray);\n```\nThe frontend's `TestWalletProvider` reads `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` to deterministically recreate the keypair in-browser.\n\n**Usage**:\n```typescript\ntest(\"devnet lifecycle\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => {\n  // playerAPage and playerBPage are already in devnet context\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Devnet Smoke Test** (`smoke.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Pre-flight validation that devnet environment is ready.\n\n**Three Tests**:\n\n1. **Deployments Reachable**\n   - Calls `verifyDevnetDeployments(devnetConfig)`\n   - Checks: RPC health, coinflip/platform/orao programs deployed, VRF initialized\n\n2. **App Loads**\n   - Navigates to `/`\n   - Expects `<body>` not empty\n   - Expects nav/sidebar visible (proves React rendered)\n\n3. **Wallet Auto-Connects**\n   - Navigates to `/`\n   - Waits for wallet to auto-connect via `TestWalletProvider`\n   - Verifies pubkey short form (first 4 chars) appears in UI\n\n---\n\n## 4. **Devnet Environment Helpers** (`env.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Validate env contract before any devnet test runs.\n\n**Required Env Vars**:\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL              — Devnet RPC endpoint (https URL)\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed coinflip program address (base58)\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed platform program address (base58)\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK       — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\n```\n\n**Validation**:\n- `validateDevnetEnv()`: Reads + validates all env vars; throws consolidated error if any missing/malformed\n- Parses base58 addresses → `PublicKey`\n- Parses URLs → checks http(s) protocol\n- Returns: `DevnetConfig` interface\n\n**Deployment Verification**:\n```typescript\nexport async function verifyDevnetDeployments(config: DevnetConfig) {\n  // 1. RPC health check (getLatestBlockhash)\n  // 2. Coinflip program deployed & executable\n  // 3. Platform program deployed & executable\n  // 4. Orao VRF program deployed & executable\n  // 5. Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF initialized)\n}\n```\n\n**Orao VRF Program ID** (hardcoded, same on all clusters):\n```\nVRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **Page Object Helpers** (`page-objects.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Reusable Playwright selectors and page-object actions for coinflip UI.\n\n**CSS-Class Selectors** (examples):\n```typescript\n.coinflip-lobby\n.coinflip-sidebar\n.rng-tier-selector\n.rng-tier-btn--selected\n.coinflip-side-btn--heads\n.coinflip-side-btn--selected\n.coinflip-matches__list\n.coinflip-match-card\n.coinflip-match-card--own\n.coinflip-active-match\n.coinflip-active-match__title--won\n.coinflip-active-match__title--lost\n.coinflip-result__outcome\n```\n\n**Page-Object Actions**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `navigateToCoinflip(page)` | Goto `/coinflip`, wait for main visible |\n| `selectTier(page, tier)` | Click tier button, expect selected class |\n| `selectSide(page, side)` | Click heads/tails button, expect selected class |\n| `createMatch(page, tier, side)` | Select tier + side, click \"Create Game\", wait for active match |\n| `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` | Find joinable match card, click join btn, wait for active match |\n| `cancelMatch(page)` | Click \"Cancel Match\", wait for lobby |\n| `claimOrSettle(page)` | Click claim/settle btn in sidebar, wait for \"Back to Lobby\" |\n| `backToLobby(page)` | Click \"Back to Lobby\", wait for lobby visible |\n\n**Wait/Assert Primitives**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` | Wait sidebar status text (e.g., \"Complete\") |\n| `waitForResult(page, timeout)` | Wait for won/lost title class, return \"won\" or \"lost\" |\n| `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)` | Wait for non-claimable match card visible |\n| `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)` | Assert zero non-claimable match cards |\n| `assertErrorToast(page, substring, timeout)` | Assert error toast contains text |\n| `assertNoErrorToast(page)` | Assert zero error toasts |\n| `waitForText(page, text, timeout)` | Wait for text visible anywhere |\n| `waitForLobby(page, timeout)` | Wait for lobby visible |\n\n**Console Error Tracking**:\n```typescript\nconst consoleA = trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n// ... run test ...\nconsoleA.assertClean(); // Fails if any non-browser-noise console errors\n```\n\nFilters out known noise (favicon, fonts, third-party cookies).\n\n---\n\n## 6. **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: RPC-based assertions for match PDA state, treasury fees, player profiles.\n\n**Program IDs** (read from IDL):\n```typescript\nCOINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address)\nPLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address)\nFEE_BPS = 300 // 3% total\n```\n\n**PDA Derivation**:\n```typescript\ngetMatchPda(creator)              // Seeds: [\"match\", creator]\ngetConfigPda()                    // Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet)       // Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]\n```\n\n**Program Instances** (read-only):\n```typescript\ngetCoinflipProgram(connection)    // Creates Program<Coinflip> via AnchorProvider\ngetPlatformProgram(connection)    // Creates Program<Platform> via AnchorProvider\n```\n\n**Account Shapes**:\n```typescript\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: Record<string, object>;  // e.g., { \"waiting\": {} }\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n\ninterface PlayerProfileAccount {\n  authority: PublicKey;\n  totalGames: { toNumber(): number };\n  wins: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWagered: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWon: { toNumber(): number };\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Fetch Helpers**:\n```typescript\nfetchMatch(connection, matchPda)              // null if closed\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda)    // null if doesn't exist\ngetTreasuryAddress(connection)                // Reads from coinflip config\n```\n\n**Balance Helpers**:\n```typescript\ngetBalanceLamports(connection, address)       // Native SOL balance\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address)          // Alias for above (for clarity)\n```\n\n**Fee Calculation**:\n```typescript\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount) => {\n  const pool = entryAmount * 2;\n  const fee = Math.floor((pool * FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n  const payout = pool - fee;\n  return { pool, fee, payout };\n}\n```\nExample: 5M entry → 10M pool → 30k fee (3%) → 9.97M payout.\n\n**Assertion Helpers**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` | Verify match PDA in \"waiting\" phase with correct tier/side/no opponent |\n| `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` | Verify match PDA account is closed (null fetch) |\n| `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` | Verify treasury balance delta matches expected fee (3% of pool) |\n| `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)` | Verify player profile stats match exact values |\n| `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)` | Verify player profile stats changed by delta |\n| `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` | Snapshot current stats (returns zeros if profile doesn't exist) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. **Wallet Helpers** (`wallets.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Deterministic keypair generation and wallet funding.\n\n**Deterministic Keypairs**:\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n```\nSame seeds always produce same keypairs (reproducible tests).\n\n**Wallet Funding**:\n```typescript\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10)\n  // Airdrop SOL + confirm transaction\n\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL, solAmount = 10)\n  // Airdrop to both PLAYER_A and PLAYER_B in parallel\n  // Verifies balances >= expected\n  // Returns { playerA, playerB, connection }\n```\n\n**Local RPC URL**: `\"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"` (local test validator default)\n\n---\n\n## 8. **Playwright Devnet Config** (`playwright.devnet.config.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Playwright config for devnet E2E tests.\n\n**Key Settings**:\n```typescript\ntestDir: \"./e2e\"\ntestMatch: \"devnet/**/*.spec.ts\"\nfullyParallel: false\nworkers: 1\nretries: 0\ntimeout: 120_000  // 120s — real VRF fulfillment can take 30–60+ seconds\n\nbaseURL: \"http://localhost:3003\"\nviewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 }\nscreenshot: \"off\"\ntrace: \"retain-on-failure\"\n```\n\n**Web Server**:\n```typescript\ncommand: \"npx vite --port 3003\"\nreuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI\nenv: {\n  VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",      // Use real on-chain\n  VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",     // Enable TestWalletProvider\n  // RPC URL + program IDs inherited from process env\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Test Patterns & Best Practices\n\n### 1. **Dual-Context Architecture**\n- Each player runs in isolated `BrowserContext` with injected keypair\n- Allows testing multi-player interactions without orchestration\n- Keypair injected via `addInitScript` → frontend reads `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n\n### 2. **Deterministic Outcomes**\n- Fixed keypair seeds → reproducible across runs\n- Local mock VRF with pre-loaded randomness → predictable results\n- Devnet uses real VRF → longer timeouts (30–60s) required\n\n### 3. **Separation of Concerns**\n- **Page Objects** (`page-objects.ts`) handle UI interaction selectors + timeouts\n- **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`) handle RPC queries, PDA derivation, assertions\n- **Wallets** (`wallets.ts`) handle keypair generation + airdrop\n\n### 4. **Snapshot-Then-Assert Pattern**\n```typescript\n// Capture state before action\nconst before = await snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet);\n\n// Perform action (claim payout)\nawait po.claimOrSettle(playerPage);\n\n// Assert state changed by expected delta\nawait assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, {\n  totalGames: 1,\n  wins: 1,\n  totalWagered: ENTRY_AMOUNT,\n  totalWon: payout,\n});\n```\n\n### 5. **Console Error Tracking**\n```typescript\nconst console = trackConsoleErrors(page);\n// ... test ...\nconsole.assertClean(); // Fails if unexpected JS errors\n```\n\n### 6. **Timeout Scaling**\n- Local tests: 10–30s timeouts (mock VRF instant)\n- Devnet tests: 30–60s+ timeouts (real VRF fulfillment)\n- Config: `timeout: 120_000` (2 min base per test)\n\n### 7. **Pre-Test Setup**\n- **Local**: `test.beforeAll()` funds wallets via airdrop\n- **Devnet**: `verifyDevnetDeployments()` runs in smoke test; wallets pre-funded off-chain\n\n---\n\n## Running Tests Locally vs Devnet\n\n**Local Lifecycle Test**:\n```bash\n# Prerequisites:\n# 1. Local validator running with programs deployed\n# 2. Mock VRF + Orao accounts initialized\n\npnpm test:e2e:local\n```\n\n**Devnet Smoke Test**:\n```bash\n# Prerequisites:\n# 1. Programs deployed to devnet\n# 2. VRF initialized\n# 3. Env vars set:\nexport VITE_RPC_URL=\"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\nexport VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=\"<deployed_address>\"\nexport VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=\"<deployed_address>\"\n\npnpm test:e2e:devnet\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive summary covers the exact APIs, patterns, imports, and signatures available in the E2E test suite. You now have a complete blueprint for writing additional devnet lifecycle tests or other E2E scenarios."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4739f12b630073b4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49464\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 45946</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"0a721dce-4519-4bfc-87a9-c96bc292eeab","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing E2E test patterns for a devnet lifecycle test. Please read and summarize these files thoroughly:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` - the local lifecycle test\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` - devnet fixtures\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts` - devnet smoke test\n4. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` - devnet env helpers\n5. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` - page object helpers\n6. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` - on-chain helpers\n7. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` - wallet helpers\n8. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` - devnet config\n\nFor each file, provide: the full content so I can understand the exact APIs, patterns, imports, and helper signatures available.","agentId":"a4739f12b630073b4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the files. Let me now provide you with a comprehensive summary of the E2E test patterns.\n\n---\n\n## E2E Test Patterns Summary\n\n### Overview\nThe codebase uses **Playwright** for E2E testing with two distinct modes:\n1. **Local**: Uses a local Solana validator with mock VRF\n2. **Devnet**: Connects to real devnet RPC with actual VRF fulfillment\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Local Lifecycle Test** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Full game flow validation (create → join → resolve → claim) with deterministic outcomes.\n\n**Architecture**:\n- **Two isolated browser contexts** (Player A and Player B) via Playwright fixtures\n- **Deterministic keypairs**: Fixed 32-byte seeds (0xaa, 0xbb) produce same keys every run\n- **Mock VRF**: Local validator has Orao mock enabled; randomness account is pre-loaded with `byte[0] = 2` (HEADS)\n- **Pre-setup**: `test.beforeAll()` funds both players via airdrop\n\n**Test Flow**:\n```\n1. Player A navigates to coinflip\n2. Player A creates match (iron tier, HEADS)\n3. On-chain: assertMatchCreated() → verify match PDA exists\n4. Player B navigates and sees match in lobby\n5. Player B joins\n6. On-chain: snapshot treasury + player profiles\n7. Both wait for result (VRF pre-fulfilled)\n8. Verify: A won (chose HEADS), B lost\n9. Player A claims payout\n10. On-chain: assertMatchClosed() + assertTreasuryFee() + assertPlayerProfileDelta()\n11. Player A returns to lobby\n```\n\n**Key Constants**:\n- `TIER_IRON = 0`\n- `SIDE_HEADS = 0`\n- `ENTRY_AMOUNT = 5_000_000` (0.005 SOL)\n- VRF polling: 5s intervals; 3s flip animation before \"complete\" phase\n\n**On-Chain Assertions**:\n- Match PDA state changes (phase, opponent, claimed flag)\n- Treasury receives 3% fee (300 bps)\n- Player profiles updated: `totalGames`, `wins`, `totalWagered`, `totalWon`\n\n---\n\n## 2. **Devnet Fixtures** (`fixtures.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Dual-player fixture for