`)\n\n**Purpose**: Validate env contract before any devnet test runs.\n\n**Required Env Vars**:\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL              — Devnet RPC endpoint (https URL)\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed coinflip program address (base58)\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed platform program address (base58)\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK       — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\n```\n\n**Validation**:\n- `validateDevnetEnv()`: Reads + validates all env vars; throws consolidated error if any missing/malformed\n- Parses base58 addresses → `PublicKey`\n- Parses URLs → checks http(s) protocol\n- Returns: `DevnetConfig` interface\n\n**Deployment Verification**:\n```typescript\nexport async function verifyDevnetDeployments(config: DevnetConfig) {\n  // 1. RPC health check (getLatestBlockhash)\n  // 2. Coinflip program deployed & executable\n  // 3. Platform program deployed & executable\n  // 4. Orao VRF program deployed & executable\n  // 5. Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF initialized)\n}\n```\n\n**Orao VRF Program ID** (hardcoded, same on all clusters):\n```\nVRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **Page Object Helpers** (`page-objects.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Reusable Playwright selectors and page-object actions for coinflip UI.\n\n**CSS-Class Selectors** (examples):\n```typescript\n.coinflip-lobby\n.coinflip-sidebar\n.rng-tier-selector\n.rng-tier-btn--selected\n.coinflip-side-btn--heads\n.coinflip-side-btn--selected\n.coinflip-matches__list\n.coinflip-match-card\n.coinflip-match-card--own\n.coinflip-active-match\n.coinflip-active-match__title--won\n.coinflip-active-match__title--lost\n.coinflip-result__outcome\n```\n\n**Page-Object Actions**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `navigateToCoinflip(page)` | Goto `/coinflip`, wait for main visible |\n| `selectTier(page, tier)` | Click tier button, expect selected class |\n| `selectSide(page, side)` | Click heads/tails button, expect selected class |\n| `createMatch(page, tier, side)` | Select tier + side, click \"Create Game\", wait for active match |\n| `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` | Find joinable match card, click join btn, wait for active match |\n| `cancelMatch(page)` | Click \"Cancel Match\", wait for lobby |\n| `claimOrSettle(page)` | Click claim/settle btn in sidebar, wait for \"Back to Lobby\" |\n| `backToLobby(page)` | Click \"Back to Lobby\", wait for lobby visible |\n\n**Wait/Assert Primitives**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` | Wait sidebar status text (e.g., \"Complete\") |\n| `waitForResult(page, timeout)` | Wait for won/lost title class, return \"won\" or \"lost\" |\n| `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)` | Wait for non-claimable match card visible |\n| `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)` | Assert zero non-claimable match cards |\n| `assertErrorToast(page, substring, timeout)` | Assert error toast contains text |\n| `assertNoErrorToast(page)` | Assert zero error toasts |\n| `waitForText(page, text, timeout)` | Wait for text visible anywhere |\n| `waitForLobby(page, timeout)` | Wait for lobby visible |\n\n**Console Error Tracking**:\n```typescript\nconst consoleA = trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n// ... run test ...\nconsoleA.assertClean(); // Fails if any non-browser-noise console errors\n```\n\nFilters out known noise (favicon, fonts, third-party cookies).\n\n---\n\n## 6. **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: RPC-based assertions for match PDA state, treasury fees, player profiles.\n\n**Program IDs** (read from IDL):\n```typescript\nCOINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address)\nPLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address)\nFEE_BPS = 300 // 3% total\n```\n\n**PDA Derivation**:\n```typescript\ngetMatchPda(creator)              // Seeds: [\"match\", creator]\ngetConfigPda()                    // Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet)       // Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]\n```\n\n**Program Instances** (read-only):\n```typescript\ngetCoinflipProgram(connection)    // Creates Program<Coinflip> via AnchorProvider\ngetPlatformProgram(connection)    // Creates Program<Platform> via AnchorProvider\n```\n\n**Account Shapes**:\n```typescript\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: Record<string, object>;  // e.g., { \"waiting\": {} }\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n\ninterface PlayerProfileAccount {\n  authority: PublicKey;\n  totalGames: { toNumber(): number };\n  wins: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWagered: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWon: { toNumber(): number };\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Fetch Helpers**:\n```typescript\nfetchMatch(connection, matchPda)              // null if closed\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda)    // null if doesn't exist\ngetTreasuryAddress(connection)                // Reads from coinflip config\n```\n\n**Balance Helpers**:\n```typescript\ngetBalanceLamports(connection, address)       // Native SOL balance\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address)          // Alias for above (for clarity)\n```\n\n**Fee Calculation**:\n```typescript\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount) => {\n  const pool = entryAmount * 2;\n  const fee = Math.floor((pool * FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n  const payout = pool - fee;\n  return { pool, fee, payout };\n}\n```\nExample: 5M entry → 10M pool → 30k fee (3%) → 9.97M payout.\n\n**Assertion Helpers**:\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` | Verify match PDA in \"waiting\" phase with correct tier/side/no opponent |\n| `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` | Verify match PDA account is closed (null fetch) |\n| `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` | Verify treasury balance delta matches expected fee (3% of pool) |\n| `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)` | Verify player profile stats match exact values |\n| `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)` | Verify player profile stats changed by delta |\n| `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` | Snapshot current stats (returns zeros if profile doesn't exist) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. **Wallet Helpers** (`wallets.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Deterministic keypair generation and wallet funding.\n\n**Deterministic Keypairs**:\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n```\nSame seeds always produce same keypairs (reproducible tests).\n\n**Wallet Funding**:\n```typescript\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10)\n  // Airdrop SOL + confirm transaction\n\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL, solAmount = 10)\n  // Airdrop to both PLAYER_A and PLAYER_B in parallel\n  // Verifies balances >= expected\n  // Returns { playerA, playerB, connection }\n```\n\n**Local RPC URL**: `\"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"` (local test validator default)\n\n---\n\n## 8. **Playwright Devnet Config** (`playwright.devnet.config.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Playwright config for devnet E2E tests.\n\n**Key Settings**:\n```typescript\ntestDir: \"./e2e\"\ntestMatch: \"devnet/**/*.spec.ts\"\nfullyParallel: false\nworkers: 1\nretries: 0\ntimeout: 120_000  // 120s — real VRF fulfillment can take 30–60+ seconds\n\nbaseURL: \"http://localhost:3003\"\nviewport: { width: 1280, height: 1080 }\nscreenshot: \"off\"\ntrace: \"retain-on-failure\"\n```\n\n**Web Server**:\n```typescript\ncommand: \"npx vite --port 3003\"\nreuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI\nenv: {\n  VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\",      // Use real on-chain\n  VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\",     // Enable TestWalletProvider\n  // RPC URL + program IDs inherited from process env\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Test Patterns & Best Practices\n\n### 1. **Dual-Context Architecture**\n- Each player runs in isolated `BrowserContext` with injected keypair\n- Allows testing multi-player interactions without orchestration\n- Keypair injected via `addInitScript` → frontend reads `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n\n### 2. **Deterministic Outcomes**\n- Fixed keypair seeds → reproducible across runs\n- Local mock VRF with pre-loaded randomness → predictable results\n- Devnet uses real VRF → longer timeouts (30–60s) required\n\n### 3. **Separation of Concerns**\n- **Page Objects** (`page-objects.ts`) handle UI interaction selectors + timeouts\n- **On-Chain Helpers** (`on-chain.ts`) handle RPC queries, PDA derivation, assertions\n- **Wallets** (`wallets.ts`) handle keypair generation + airdrop\n\n### 4. **Snapshot-Then-Assert Pattern**\n```typescript\n// Capture state before action\nconst before = await snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet);\n\n// Perform action (claim payout)\nawait po.claimOrSettle(playerPage);\n\n// Assert state changed by expected delta\nawait assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, {\n  totalGames: 1,\n  wins: 1,\n  totalWagered: ENTRY_AMOUNT,\n  totalWon: payout,\n});\n```\n\n### 5. **Console Error Tracking**\n```typescript\nconst console = trackConsoleErrors(page);\n// ... test ...\nconsole.assertClean(); // Fails if unexpected JS errors\n```\n\n### 6. **Timeout Scaling**\n- Local tests: 10–30s timeouts (mock VRF instant)\n- Devnet tests: 30–60s+ timeouts (real VRF fulfillment)\n- Config: `timeout: 120_000` (2 min base per test)\n\n### 7. **Pre-Test Setup**\n- **Local**: `test.beforeAll()` funds wallets via airdrop\n- **Devnet**: `verifyDevnetDeployments()` runs in smoke test; wallets pre-funded off-chain\n\n---\n\n## Running Tests Locally vs Devnet\n\n**Local Lifecycle Test**:\n```bash\n# Prerequisites:\n# 1. Local validator running with programs deployed\n# 2. Mock VRF + Orao accounts initialized\n\npnpm test:e2e:local\n```\n\n**Devnet Smoke Test**:\n```bash\n# Prerequisites:\n# 1. Programs deployed to devnet\n# 2. VRF initialized\n# 3. Env vars set:\nexport VITE_RPC_URL=\"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\nexport VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=\"<deployed_address>\"\nexport VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=\"<deployed_address>\"\n\npnpm test:e2e:devnet\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive summary covers the exact APIs, patterns, imports, and signatures available in the E2E test suite. You now have a complete blueprint for writing additional devnet lifecycle tests or other E2E scenarios."}],"totalDurationMs":45946,"totalTokens":49464,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20200,"cache_read_input_tokens":24775,"output_tokens":4482,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20200,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XoUyTDJ2Ff9wmkxqpGTxEX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me now implement the devnet lifecycle test. Key differences from local:\n\n1. No mock VRF - uses real VRF request/fulfillment\n2. No local bootstrap/teardown\n3. Longer timeouts for VRF fulfillment\n4. No program config initialization (already deployed)\n5. Need to fund wallets on devnet (airdrop may be rate-limited)\n\nLet me look at the local lifecycle test more closely and the devnet fixtures to write the devnet lifecycle test. Let me also check what `localnet-setup.ts` does since the devnet won't need that initialization step.\n\n\nI'm examining the local lifecycle test to understand the full pattern and structure I need to replicate for devnet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5181,"cache_read_input_tokens":49314,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5181},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"27878c74-d577-4fd5-9242-83ad6f979915"}
