{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014iXeKQmSBkTcK6zhDyrNg9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Devnet E2E smoke test.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Validates the devnet environment contract (env vars + deployed programs)\n     5→ * and verifies the app loads against the devnet RPC.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n     8→import { verifyDevnetDeployments } from \"./helpers/env\";\n     9→\n    10→test.describe(\"devnet smoke\", () => {\n    11→  test(\"devnet deployments are reachable and valid\", async ({\n    12→    devnetConfig,\n    13→  }) => {\n    14→    // Verifies: RPC health, coinflip/platform/orao programs deployed, VRF initialized\n    15→    await verifyDevnetDeployments(devnetConfig);\n    16→  });\n    17→\n    18→  test(\"app loads against devnet\", async ({ playerAPage }) => {\n    19→    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    20→    // App should render the main layout (not a blank screen or error page)\n    21→    await expect(playerAPage.locator(\"body\")).not.toBeEmpty();\n    22→    // Navigation should be present (proves React rendered)\n    23→    await expect(\n    24→      playerAPage.locator(\"nav, [class*='sidebar'], [class*='nav']\").first(),\n    25→    ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n    26→  });\n    27→\n    28→  test(\"wallet connects with test keypair on devnet\", async ({\n    29→    playerAPage,\n    30→    playerAKeypair,\n    31→  }) => {\n    32→    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    33→    // Wait for wallet to auto-connect via TestWalletProvider\n    34→    const pubkeyShort = playerAKeypair.publicKey.toBase58().slice(0, 4);\n    35→    // The wallet address (or a truncated version) should appear somewhere in the UI\n    36→    await expect(playerAPage.getByText(pubkeyShort).first()).toBeVisible({\n    37→      timeout: 15_000,\n    38→    });\n    39→  });\n    40→});\n    41→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7881ac6-ae6b-4bf4-983d-8efe2357b0da","uuid":"c24eb330-1083-4a54-970a-15085bba24b1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts","content":"/**\n * Devnet E2E smoke test.\n *\n * Validates the devnet environment contract (env vars + deployed programs)\n * and verifies the app loads against the devnet RPC.\n */\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport { verifyDevnetDeployments } from \"./helpers/env\";\n\ntest.describe(\"devnet smoke\", () => {\n  test(\"devnet deployments are reachable and valid\", async ({\n    devnetConfig,\n  }) => {\n    // Verifies: RPC health, coinflip/platform/orao programs deployed, VRF initialized\n    await verifyDevnetDeployments(devnetConfig);\n  });\n\n  test(\"app loads against devnet\", async ({ playerAPage }) => {\n    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    // App should render the main layout (not a blank screen or error page)\n    await expect(playerAPage.locator(\"body\")).not.toBeEmpty();\n    // Navigation should be present (proves React rendered)\n    await expect(\n      playerAPage.locator(\"nav, [class*='sidebar'], [class*='nav']\").first(),\n    ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n  });\n\n  test(\"wallet connects with test keypair on devnet\", async ({\n    playerAPage,\n    playerAKeypair,\n  }) => {\n    await playerAPage.goto(\"/\");\n    // Wait for wallet to auto-connect via TestWalletProvider\n    const pubkeyShort = playerAKeypair.publicKey.toBase58().slice(0, 4);\n    // The wallet address (or a truncated version) should appear somewhere in the UI\n    await expect(playerAPage.getByText(pubkeyShort).first()).toBeVisible({\n      timeout: 15_000,\n    });\n  });\n});\n","numLines":41,"startLine":1,"totalLines":41}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01APtt3y1b9ZHYV9pLP14P3i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have everything I need. Let me create the devnet lifecycle test. Key design decisions:\n\n1. **Non-deterministic outcome**: Since real VRF is used, we don't know who wins. The test must handle either outcome.\n2. **Wallet funding on devnet**: Need to airdrop SOL to test wallets. Devnet airdrop can be rate-limited but should work for small amounts.\n3. **VRF fulfillment wait**: Need longer timeout (60-90s) since real VRF can take time. Polling/backoff is the next checklist item so I'll use basic wait patterns here.\n\n\n4. **No on-chain assertions here**: Those are a separate checklist item.\n5. **Use page-objects from local/helpers**: They're shared utilities.\n\nI'm creating the devnet lifecycle test file and need to handle wallet funding with airdrop, accounting for devnet's rate limiting. I'll need to either create a devnet-specific funding function or adapt the existing one to accept a custom RPC endpoint instead of defaulting to the local one.\n\nFor the VRF test, I need to remember that \"no mock resolve shortcut\" means the test waits for the actual Orao VRF callback rather than programmatically setting the result. Let me write the test file now.\n\nI'll structure it similarly to the local lifecycle test but adapted for devnet: using devnet fixtures, funding wallets with a smaller SOL amount and retry logic since airdrop is rate-limited, skipping the local initialization since programs are already deployed, handling non-deterministic outcomes since either player can win, using longer timeouts for VRF callbacks, and verifying the winner claims and UI state updates correctly. I'll also need a helper for devnet wallet funding since the local airdrop approach won't work reliably there.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input